transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Clint speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I wish to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: What's your zip code?

Speaker 2: What's that?

Speaker 1: Your zip code?

Speaker 2: 49094.

Speaker 1: What's your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Tim Carpenter.

Speaker 1: Alrighty, and do you mind if I ask why it is you're canceling the Viagra today, sir?

Speaker 2: Because I was only supposed to be trying it, and it wasn't supposed to be a prescription.

Speaker 1: Yeah, all you got to do is set this up, sir. I mean, it's obviously a prescription.

Speaker 2: Well, yeah, I mean, I know that, but it was supposed to be just a one-time order.

Speaker 1: Yeah, as long as you set that up, sir, that's fine. You can set it up to order as needed.

Speaker 2: That's an option. We give those options when you purchase this.

Speaker 1: Yeah, well, that's what I did, and it's not working. I just want to cancel it.

Speaker 2: Well, you don't want to just order it as needed?

Speaker 1: No, I want to cancel it.

Speaker 2: And that's because it's not working?

Speaker 1: I've already got a prescription through my doctor for that stuff,

Speaker 2: and this stuff that I'm getting from you guys is not what was advertised.

Speaker 1: So I just want to cancel it.

Speaker 2: So what was advertised? What did you think you were getting, sir?

Speaker 1: Dude, I just want to cancel the prescription, all right, please?

Speaker 2: Look, I'm trying to help you out, sir.

Speaker 1: I don't want your help. I just want your help in canceling it.

Speaker 2: All right, sir. Have a good day. We'll cancel it for you. Have a good one.

Speaker 1: Yep.
